  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together flour, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and ground spices.",
    "Add in the chopped cranberries and mix until combined.",
    "Add in the unsalted butter and mix until a dough forms.",
    "Press the dough evenly into a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, or until the edges are lightly golden.",
    "While the crust is baking, prepare the glassy-jelly topping by whisking together the orange marmalade and sherry in a bowl.",
    "After the crust has baked for 20 minutes, remove it from the oven and spread the glassy-jelly topping evenly over the top.",
    "Return the dish to the oven and bake for an additional 15-20 minutes, or until the jelly is set and the crust is golden brown."
  ],
